description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a highly motivated and flexible person to join the Health Records Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be flexible and able to adjust to the requirements of the service to cover other sites within the Trust and various shifts, which will include weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a very busy department covering Central Health Records Library based at Cobalt, satellite library based at Wansbeck General Hospital and the Reception Areas at Hexham, North Tyneside and Wansbeck General Hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The reception areas include, dependent upon site, Main Outpatients, Gynaecology, Antenatal, Main Reception, Wansbeck Clinic, Surgical Day Unit, Fracture Clinic and the Medical Records Office. The role involves the production, maintenance and custody of both manual and computerised records.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Criteria:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educated to NVQ level 2 or equivalent English and Mathematics or be able to demonstrate good numeracy or literacy skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good knowledge of the Data Protection Act&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working/dealing with the public&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understands the need for the patient record to be at the right place at the right time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
